Started having babies at hardly 14 years of age, pitied, demeaned, disparaged and written off as a loser, but through the grace of God, I never gave up. Thanks to my mother and all the ancestors before me for their prayers! #anachihera

This song tells my story in a way that makes me cry with a kind of joy that comes from the deepest part of my belly. 

In summary, in this song, Chief Hwenje & Obert Chari remind us that despite our circumstances, our past or even what the naysayers say, the heavens always remain loyal to our cause.

 You’re a gift, a blessing, and within you there are immeasurable deep wellsprings of wealth and talents that can bring joy and healing to the world.

 Enjoy the song. And here are 2 campaigns that you can follow and support.

These awards recognize the achievements and contributions of women, highlighting their impact on society and inspiring others to follow in their footsteps.

They help to increase the visibility of women and their work, bringing attention to their cause and raising awareness about issues that matter to them.

By celebrating women and their accomplishments, these awards help to empower other women and girls, showing them that they too can make a difference and have a positive impact on the world.

These awards serve as inspiration to future generations of women, showing them that they can achieve their dreams and make a positive impact, regardless of gender.

These awards play a crucial role in promoting gender equality and empowering women and girls to lead positive change in their communities and the world at large.

Something has been brewing… The 2024 Awakened Woman Global Leadership Tour!
 
Mark and I are hosting an 8–day leadership tour in Zimbabwe. A truly life-changing experience.

The 9th – 17th June 2024 tour will be a once in a lifetime experience to visit and interact with the TTI Foundation supported rural schools and get to know the local people and their rich culture. The tour will culminate with a visit to one of the seven greatest natural wonders of the world, Victoria falls. The excursion to Victoria Falls includes a day trip to one of Africa’s most famous National Parks that contains the world’s largest elephants.

 🌟Accommodation, meals, and ground transport as well as plane tickets from Harare to Victoria Falls are inclusive in the package. Apply to learn more and details will be send to you🌟
 
The exposure to the rich African traditions of my rural village, and the excursion to Victoria falls curate an education and safari experience like no other! 
 

Applications for the 2024 Awakened Woman Global Leadership Tours are now open. See link in my bio.

 https://tereraitrentteachings.org/global-leadership-tours/

The 2024 Awakened Woman 8 Day Global Leadership Tour! 

What Day 1 & 2 will look like🌟

Day 1. On arrival at the Harare international Airport in Zimbabwe, Mark & I will meet you and transfer you to your accommodation. We are your hosts!
Day 2. After tasty breakfast, we have a leadership workshop and you will work with me and my team on leadership and we will introduce you to some of our Foundation’s initiatives. 
In the afternoon we go for a hike through a local woodland and enjoy the afternoon with zebras, giraffes etc.
In the evening we all sit by the open fire and reflect on the day’s events.

Don’t forget to submit your application and share something about yourself.
 See link in bio
 https://tereraitrentteachings.org/global-leadership-tours/

It was absolutely magical!

Just landed at IAD after hosting an 8 day Awakened Woman Global Leadership tour for a group of 18 Students from Oklahoma State University @okstate_plc 

It was truly amazing to watch TTI students and OSU students singing, playing and interacting with each other. 

In a million years I couldn’t have imagined this one!

This is a bit emotional for me…

 As I reflect back on the years of my undergrad and master’s at Oklahoma State University (OSU), I couldn’t see OSU students coming to my village, and let alone becoming part of my 5th dream that I buried more than 2 decades ago—to give back to my community and improve the lives of women and girls…” And indeed, through @wishesforwater , a student led initiative, the OSU students provided a solar powered water well at one of our rural primary schools.

The laughter, the comradeship, and the joy of Ubuntu amongst the students was EVERYTHING. 

God almighty is great! 

Thank you Josh and Tashia for your leadership🥲. Oh my word, my gratitude, my warm regards to OSU and it’s leadership🧡🙏🌟
@wishesforwater @thewomenchangingtheworld @jeraaled @tti_foundation

The 8-Day Leadership Tour—We hosted a group of 18 Students from Oklahoma State University @okstate_plc 

After a night of rest in Harare, the capital city of Zimbabwe, we took the group on a 2-day visit to TTI Foundation supported rural schools where the students witnessed the drilling of a school water well funded by @wishesforwater. Many of the students on this tour were members of the Wishes for Water organization. One evening, the tour group joined the local community in “water dance”  to celebrate another water well funded by @TTI  for the community.  It was also an opportunity for the group to know the local people and their rich culture. 
The tour culminated with a visit to one of the seven greatest natural wonders of the world, Victoria falls. The excursion to Victoria Falls included a day trip to one of Africa’s most famous National Parks that contains the world’s largest elephants. Leadership sessions and reflections were crosscutting themes throughout the tour.

They say, once Africa gets into your blood you will never be the same😜

It was absolutely magical. The Awakened Woman Global leadership Tours are one of the best adventures never to be missed. 
Go to my bio to learn more about our upcoming 2024 Awakened Woman 8-day leadership tour.

The Awakened Woman Global leadership Tours are one of the best adventures never to be missed.

What can I say, @sarah_makoni is one of our sponsored students and soon to be graduating. Last Sunday I woke up to Sarah’s message—humbling…but it’s all because of you our supporters!

“Greetings Dr. Trent 
As I sit down to write this message, I am filled with gratitude and a deep sense of appreciation towards you. 

You took me out of the rural area and allowed me to pursue higher education at the university. Today, as I am about to graduate, I cannot thank you enough for the profound impact you have had on my life.

I remember the day you came into my life and saw something in me that I did not even see in myself. 
You believed in me and my potential, and you gave me the support and encouragement I needed to make my dreams a reality. 

Your unwavering faith in me has been a constant source of motivation, and it has propelled me to work harder and strive for excellence.

The education and experiences I have gained at the university have been transformative, and I have grown in ways I never thought possible. I owe all of this to you, and I want you to know that I am forever grateful for the opportunities you have provided me.

As I prepare to graduate and enter the next phase of my life, I will carry the lessons and values you have instilled in me. I will always remember your kindness, generosity, and belief in me, and I will strive to pay it forward by making a positive impact in the world.

Thank you once again for everything you have done for me. You have made a profound difference in my life, and I will always be grateful to you.

Sincerely,
Sarah Makoni”

@wishesforwater partners with @tti_foundation to bring safe and reliable water to Hurungwe district. @sonrisabebo speaks to importance of this partnership.

A leadership tour in Zimbabwe that stays in your heart. 

Come and join me in June 2024 for a unique leadership tour where you will experience sustainable leadership in action at work. 

You will also get to see the wonders of Africa including the magnificent Victoria Falls, a safari in Chobe National Park, as well as a spectacular river cruise dinner on the Zambezi River. 

Places are limited and filling fast let us know today if you’d like more information about this lifechanging tour.

You have a full year to make payments for your place. 

A package information with details has already been sent, please check your emails.

The event at @kripalucenter in Stockbridge, MA took me 3 weeks to process. It was radical, epic and the reciprocation of the message was soul grounding. My friend @elizabeth_gilbert_writer and I offered an Awakening Magic ….. wow, I don’t even know what to call it. It was spiritually invoking and yet grounding. I felt the Kripalu grounds shaking with the vibrations of ancient sounds. The participants, mainly women seemed ready for the message. Liz and I were just gatekeepers creating a safe space for the MAGIC to roam the place. And indeed, it was BIG, MAGICAL and SACRED. They were times when one could hear the sound of a pin dropping, and times the sound of dancing feet and laughter echoing through the sacred grounds of Kripalu.  Ultimately, each woman came home to herself. The birthing and awakening of silenced dreams reverberated beyond the Kripalu Walls.
Thank you kripalu for the space, thank Liz for everything, and thank you to all in attendance and thank you giving yourself permission to do YOU.  Many of those in attendance expressed interest to join our June 2024 Awakened Woman Tour, please get hold of @peace.mitchell @alexmtchell @katypartygirl to make arrangements for your spot. This is a highly anticipated tour with limited spots, get yours before it’s too late.

@today.i.noticed book by Willow and Deborah will change the way you experience the world. Their social media and that of @sketchymuma grounded me during Covid and helped me to notice and appreciate the smallest moments in every day life. “Today I notice is a must book to have in your home. The authors captured the collective pulse of the world with humor and sweetness, ultimately reminding us that even the behaviors of the tiniest ants are worth noticing. I’m grateful for the jam packed wisdom that this book carries. I have no doubt you will find the wisdom in this book worth your time.

What can I say!
This one is for you. It’s from the father of one of our recent graduates, Sarah Makoni. 

To you all who continue to support @tti_foundation , and to you who never tire of cheering us, and to you who unequivocally give us your shoulders to cry on and hid to our call as we carry our mission, this prayer from Sarah’s father is for you. 

Indeed, may the universe continue to bless you.

I was surprised with this unsolicited heartfelt message!

To learn more about our work, please visit our website: www.Tererai.org

A Prayer—A Dry Borehole

🛐“Let him increase the number of your days here on Earth. May he keep you safe.

With water, you bring us freedom. Water is a challenge, and yet it is vital for our survival! Look at me, now old and tattered without access to water.

Look at my disabled feet, I can’t walk the long distances needed to fetch river water. 

What about the school children! They suffer without water.
Our children bring dirty water to school carried in dirty plastic bottles.

I can’t even begin to talk about the plight of our children when it comes to water. They drink water infested with diseases, cholera, whatever!
The God of Samuel that I pray to—may he give you long life and keep you safe. I pray.”🛐

“I am here, I am here, and here I am” declares @florencekayungwa, one of our students who just graduated with a degree in Radio, Television and Film Production. 

This girl is a true inspiration. Not only is Florence brilliant, entrepreneurial, she is also compassionate, and truly walks the talk—she is giving back to the community and has joined @tti_foundation in its efforts to create a better world for rural girls. 

I have known Florence since she was a young girl, she a game changer who knows how to live her dreams. 

Currently, Florence is running a campaign to provide sanitary pads for TTI supported schools in rural Zimbabwe. Watch this girl as she is showing the world the power of giving back! 
If I may say it again, Florence is the epitome of brilliance, compassionate and savvy. 

To all our donors and supporters, here is one example, and outcome, the result of your efforts and hard earned funds. And they are many who just graduated this 2023! We thank you🙏

Here is where you can support our scholarship fund and help us get more rural girls into college: https://tererai.org/2187-2/

Guess what, I’m on subtrack where I have created an open fire platform where  I invite you to come warm your souls as you listen to sacred stories. 
Stories nurtured from the deepest of bellies, narratives that hold our curiosity in awe, sometimes heartbreaking and sometimes leaving us giddy with laughter and tears of healing.

Come beloved, come my sahwiras, come dance and seep into the heroic stories that ignite the charcoals into dawn.
You can do free subscription, it’s your choice. You can also try paid subscription @$8/month, it’s your choice. The most important thing is to let the ambers of the ancestors and my Sahwiras’ storytelling warm your soul.
See link in bio
https://tererait.substack.com/

For the sisterhood here, there and everywhere —from my sahwira @stephanie_regalado_writer 

In a world brimming with chaos and uncertainty, there are moments when we come across words that have the remarkable ability to pierce through the noise and resonate with our very essence. 

Stephanie Regalado, a dear friend and an incredible writer, possesses this remarkable talent – the gift to touch the depths of our souls with her poetic expressions. 

Stephanie has an extraordinary voice and she reminds us of our humanity no mater which side of the fence we’re sitting. 

https://open.substack.com/pub/tererait/p/for-the-sisterhood-here-there-and?r=2sxd3j&utm_campaign=post&utm_medium=web

You can  find the link to my subtrack in my bio above. It is the first item on my linktree.

“Blame The Vaginas For My Blindness” — A Special Edition With My Surrogate Grandmother —In this captivating narrative, we delve into the powerful journey of personal storytelling, guided by the wisdom of my beloved surrogate grandmother.

I am confident that this narrative will inspire you to harness the potency of your own life stories by contemplating your vulnerabilities and experiences. 

Without further ado, allow me to immerse you in this captivating tale.

https://open.substack.com/pub/tererait/p/owning-our-stories?r=2sxd3j&utm_campaign=post&utm_medium=email

You can  find the link to my subtrack in my bio. It is the first item on my linktree.

Exploring the Depths of Soul Wounding: Unraveling the Invisible Scars

Dear Sahwira, 
Now that you are here, please step into the embrace of our open fire, just as you are, come and let’s explore the depths of our soul wounding. This read is powerful. It’s grounding. It helps us to unravel the invisible scars we carry, the mysterious entity that resides deep within the recesses of our being, a profound emotional or psychological injury that can reverberate through the corridors of our lives forming an insidious generational pattern.

Join our open fire at—https://tererait.substack.com/p/healing-our-collective-soul-wounds-d98

It’s Our Season to Celebrate our Graduates!📣

You’re invited to join us on December 16 at Matau School in Hurungwe as we gather to celebrate with all our students (cohort 1-3) who graduated from colleges and universities. A Heartfelt gratitude to our global donors who continue to support our efforts. 

Please come dine, feast and dance with Tererai Trent International Foundation and the community as we celebrate these milestones! 

Please let us know if you’re interested to join us. Those out of Zimbabwe we have accommodation for you.

8,500 in attendance at Illinois Association of School Boards (IASB), Chicago!

Before heading home to Zimbabwe—I’m about to speak at one of the nation's largest state education conferences conference hosted by Illinois Association of School Boards, Illinois Association of School Administrators, and Illinois Association of School Business Officials.

It’s a privilege to be one of the headliners for this conference. 

I will keep you posted on how it goes. 

All I know is that I love everything to do with Education.

I had to go in to see the space before my  speaking. Wow, it’s huge!

Part Two Healing Our Collective Soul Wounds  is out!

Come to the fire and join me on this transformative odyssey as we continue to unlock the power of our soul wounds and chart a path towards healing and resilience. Check the link in my bio! Your support for my “Dear Sahwira” message on Substack is greatly appreciated.

https://open.substack.com/pub/tererait/p/healing-our-collective-soul-wounds-b1c?r=2sxd3j&utm_campaign=post&utm_medium=web

It’s Sunday, my Sahwira.

And the storyteller takes us deep into the feminine goddess that quenches a woman’s inner thirst! Yeah, you heard me right!

Whether it’s early morning Sunday or late afternoon, please come step into the warm embrace of my open fire. 

Come just as you are, and surrender to the enchanting world of Sahwira Seynabou, as she tells a story of the “BIG O.”

This story is extraordinary, skillfully told, blending elements of awe and amusement into the very essence of our existence.

With each word, Seynabou conjures an experience of pure delight, igniting our spirit and etching an indelible mark in the hearts of those who journey through her stories.

https://tererait.substack.com/p/the-big-o-with-my-special-sahwira-c9b

See link in my bio for the story.

It’s Friday—Just for laughs 😎
I had to leave my husband at a day care at an Irish bar somewhere downtown, Dublin to run some errands. But before I left him I had to make sure he understood the memo. And I toured the pub to make sure he was safe.

Our Foundation’s $300,000 Campaign Goal Achieved!

Thank you for your generosity, we have raised $316,000 from 106 donors!

This campaign took us a long time, but we did it. Truly, truly my deepest gratitude for your continuous support. Your support is not just a donation, it's a legacy in the lives of our students and their families.

I’m truly grateful for the team behind organizing this campaign. And a huge thanks to our 116 donors. No words can express my heartfelt gratitude for helping our foundation to achieve this milestone.

On another note, we invite you to the upcoming graduation ceremony of our scholarship beneficiaries
cohorts 1 to 3, set to take place in Matau, Zimbabwe.

Details of the Graduation Ceremony are as follows:

Date: 16 December 2023
Time: 9am to 3PM
Venue: Matau Primary School, Hurungwe

This year, we are proud to celebrate over 20 graduates, each with their unique story of perseverance and triumph. 

We would be honored to have you join us as we celebrate the accomplishments of our scholars and look forward to the future they are poised to build.

And we’re on another campaign: to advance access to STEM education among our students, and especially girls, by establishing 2 science labs at 2 High Schools.

Hooray!! The Cohorts that Made History in Hurungwe, Zimbabwe! 

2023 has been a great year for TTI. This year has shown us that indeed  EDUCATION changes lives and advance the common good. 

On December 16,  2023, we held our inaugural Graduation Ceremony to celebrate twenty one (21) students who had graduated from colleges & universities since the inception of the TTI Scholarship Program.

And more than 60 students are attending colleges and universities.

It was an extraordinary event as TTI staff, its leadership, partners and the community witnessed and celebrated the graduates. These students are from the first 3 cohorts since 2017 (Cohorts 1–3). 

Drs Sarifa and Hassan Younes came all the way from Australia to attend the celebration. Dr. Sarifa Alonto Younes gave an inspiring speech as she encouraged the graduates to continue to pursue their dreams, to believe in themselves and to remain the force for good. She wowed the students.

During the ceremony, Mr Mhuma, the Provincial Education Director gave a heartfelt speech and gave our student hope. He promised to give jobs to all the graduates. Wow, what a resounding success, to have all of our graduates securing job offers for the upcoming year. 

This is a testament to hard work and dedication, and we are thrilled to see them embark on the next chapter of their professional lives.

To all our donors, fans and supporters, on behalf of the TTI board of trustees and our staff, I am beyond grateful for your support of our work. With your continued support, you make it possible for TTI to pave the way for many students to achieve their dreams. 

Indeed, to see the fruits of dreams planted and buried deep down under a rock decades ago is soul fulfilling. I’m truly humbled to know I have friends and fans like you who have followed and supported the journey.

And thanks to @oprah for making this sacred dream a reality💜💜
